    "name": "Lis Sørensen",
    "profile": "Danish singer, guitarist and songwriter born on May 28, 1955 in Brabrand, Denmark. A major female vocalist in various settings in Danish pop and rock since the middle of the 1970s.\r\n\r\nStarted her singing career as teenager in the all-girl band [a=De Fem] (appearing on record in 1970 as [a=It's So Easy]) before joining all-female rock band [a=Shit & Chanel] in 1972 with a.o. [a=Anne Linnet]. Sørensen soon established a career as one of Denmark's most popular backing vocalists, backing a.o. [a=Gasolin'], [a=Gnags] and especially [a=Sebastian (5)]. In January 1977, her mother died, which left some emotions to be resolved that affected songs, such as \"Stille Før Storm\" from [m=290050].\r\n\r\nAfter Shit & Chanel dissolved in 1979, she became part of [a=Anne Linnet Band] with Linnet and [a=Sanne Salomonsen]. In 1983, she released her first solo album [r=1278057], followed by a number of albums in her own name over the years. Sings on the charity single [m=841704] from 1985. Her solo album [m=23",
